Package: captuR
Type: Package
Title: Lightweight Object Capture and Metadata Tracking
Version: 1.5
Authors@R: c( person("Michael", "Schultz", email = "m-a-schultz@protonmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Provides a lightweight framework to automatically capture contextual metadata
    about R objects at creation time. Captured metadata includes the generating code,
    dependencies, digests, script and Git information, seeds, session info, and user-defined tags.
    Useful for reproducibility, validation, and provenance tracking. Supports capture from scripts,
    code blocks, and pipelines, and includes comparison and inspection utilities.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    CodeDepends,
    digest,
    utils,
    rstudioapi,
    gert,
    knitr
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
BugReports: https://github.com/m-a-schultz/captuR/issues
URL: https://github.com/m-a-schultz/captuR
